'''Gennady Grushevoy''' ([[Belarusian language]]: ''Генадзь Грушавы'', '''Hienadź Hrušavy''' 24 July 1950 – 28 January 2014 <ref>[http://www.svaboda.org/content/article/25245108.html]</ref>) was a [[Professor]] of [[philosophy]] at the [[Belarusian State University]] from 1973 until his death in 2014. He was elected to the [[Supreme Soviet of Belarus]] in 1990 and was a member of the [[Belarusian Popular Front]]. He was the Chairman of the board of the [[Children of Chernobyl]] from its inception in 1989. Grushevoy was the 1999 recipient of the [[Rafto Prize]].
