{{Infobox person |name = Jack Binstead |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|09|30}} |occupation = Actor |website = [http://www.jackbinstead.co.uk/home.html Official website] }}
'''Jack Binstead''' is an [[England|English]] actor best known for playing Leslie "Rem Dogg" Remmington in the [[BBC Three]] television series ''[[Bad Education (TV series)|Bad Education]]''.
== Early and Personal life == Binstead has been a [[wheelchair]] user since the age of 3,<ref>http://www.jackbinstead.co.uk/about.html</ref> as he suffers from the condition [[Osteogenesis Imperfecta]] more commonly known as brittle bone disease.
Prior to appearing in ''Bad Education'', Binstead made appearances on ''[[The Paul O'Grady Show]]''.
Binstead’s first daughter Daisy was born in 2018
== Acting career == On 11 August 2012 it was announced that Binstead would be playing the role of Leslie 'Rem Dogg' Remmington in [[Bad Education (TV series)|Bad Education]],<ref name="BBC">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/N0pWyZl9TWkBWXd3tSNW0g/rem-dogg|title=BBC Three - Bad Education, Series 1 - Rem Dogg|work=[[BBC Online]]|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref> a role he played until the series ended in October 2014.<ref name="Jeffery">{{cite web|url=http://m.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a604934/bad-education-is-school-out-forever-or-should-the-hit-comedy-return.html#~oTnsQKDSsdhka4|title=Bad Education: Is school out forever or should the hit comedy return? - TV News - Digital Spy|last=Jeffery|first=Morgan|date=21 October 2014|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref> He reprised the role in the [[The Bad Education Movie|Bad Education Movie]].
In June 2015, he appeared in two 'Blue Badge' specials of ''[[Off Their Rockers (TV series)|Off Their Rockers]]'' on [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]].
Jack also had a brief role playing Justin Palmer in the third episode of the hit comedy [[Life's Too Short (TV series)|Life's Too Short]] with [[Warwick Davis]].
