{{unreferenced|date=April 2017}}[[File:Myouken.jpg|thumb|A Myoken statue of [[Hōun-ji (Kami)|Hōun-ji]], [[Kami, Hyōgo (Mikata)|Kami]], [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo]]]]
'''Myōken''' '''Bosatsu''' ([[Sanskrit]]: Sudrsti/Sudarśana, Japanese: 妙見菩薩) or ''Hokushin-sonsei-myōken Daibosatsu'', is a [[bodhisattva]] (''bosatsu''), who is the deification of the [[North Star]]. It is mainly associated with the [[Nichiren Buddhism|Nichiren]], [[Shingon Buddhism|Shingon]] and [[Tendai]] temples. 

As god of the Polestar, he was associated with [[Amenominakanushi]]-no-kami, but also [[Kisshōten]] (one of the [[Seven Lucky Gods]]) and [[Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyōrai]] (medicine god). Myōken has always been worshipped by the Heike, and among them one of the first samurai, [[Taira-no-Masakado]]. Even today, he is still worshipped by the [[Sōma clan]]'s lords and honorary generals, as part of the rituals of ''[[Sōma Nomaoi]]''. 

