The '''Ozinie''' were a group of [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]] living on [[Kent Island, Maryland|Kent Island]], [[Maryland]] at the time that John Smith visited the island in 1608. They were an [[Algonquian languages|Algonquian]]-language tribe and were related to the [[Nanticoke tribe|Nanticoke]], another [[Algonquian languages|Algonquian]]-language tribe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fws.gov/uploadedFiles/Region_5/NWRS/South_Zone/Chesapeake_Marshlands_Complex/Eastern_Neck/EasternNeckHistory.pdf |title=History of Eastern Neck Island| publisher=[[United States Fish and Wildlife Service]] |accessdate=2014-04-11}}</ref>

