[[File:Thomas Monroe Campbell 1906 (cropped).jpg|thumb|{{center|Thomas Monroe Campbell}}]] '''Thomas Monroe Campbell''' (1883 &ndash; 1956) was the first Cooperative Extension Agent in the [[United States]] and headed the first Extension Program as a field agent for the [[U.S. Department of Agriculture]]. Well known for his work under the tutelage of [[Booker T. Washington]]<ref> {{cite book |last= Lovett |first= Laura L. |title= Conceiving the Future: Pronatalism, Reproduction, and the Family in the United States, 1890-1938 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3VZghaXeO24C&printsec=frontcover#PPA120,M1 |accessdate=2009-03-06 |edition=Illustrated |year= 2007 |publisher= UNC Press |isbn=0-8078-3107-7 |page= 120 }} </ref> and peered with [[George Washington Carver]], Campbell was also the winner of the [[William E. Harmon Foundation award for distinguished achievement among Negroes|Harmon Award]] in 1930 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuskegee.edu/Global/story.asp?S=1144384|title=Thomas Moore Campbell: Biography|publisher=Tuskegee University|accessdate=2009-03-05|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927193142/http://www.tuskegee.edu/Global/story.asp?S=1144384|archivedate=2007-09-27|df=}}</ref> for his service in the field of agriculture and author of the book ''The Movable School Goes to the Negro Farmer.'' He was a nationally known and well respected public servant of the first rank. A bust of Campbell can be found in the [[Tuskegee University]] Library.<ref>Campbell, T. M. (1969, 1936). The Movable School Goes to The Negro Farmer. New York - Tuskegee Institute: Arno Press & The New York Times - Tuskegee Institute Press.</ref><ref>Rasmussen, W. D. (1989). Taking the University to the People - Seventy-five Years of Cooperative Extension. Ames: Iowa State University.</ref>
==Family life== Campbell and his wife Anna had six children; their fourth child was [[William A. Campbell (Tuskegee Airman)|Col. William A. Campbell]], who became a highly decorated member of the [[Tuskegee Airmen]].<ref name="monterey_herald">{{cite web|title=William A. Campbell Obituary|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/montereyherald/obituary.aspx?pid=157652093|publisher=The Monterey Herald|accessdate=November 16, 2013}}</ref>
